teams.strDescriptionEN: Al-Ahli Club (Arabic: النادي الأهلي الرياضي) also known as Al Ahli Khartoum is an association football club from Khartoum, Sudan. They play in the top level of Sudanese professional football, the Sudan Premier League. Their home stadium is Khartoum Stadium.

teams.strTeamAlternate: Al Mirghani Educational Sport Club, نادي الميرغني للتربية الرياضية
teams.strDescriptionEN: Al Mirghani Educational Sport Club (Arabic: نادي الميرغني للتربية الرياضية) is a Sudanese football club based in Kassala. Their home stadium is Stade Al-Merghani Kassala. They played in the second division of the Sudanese Premier League division 2.

teams.strTeamAlternate: Al-Ahli Sports Club, Al-Ahli Wad Medani, النادي الأهلي الرياضي
teams.strDescriptionEN: Al-Ahli Sports Club (Arabic: النادي الأهلي الرياضي), also known as Al-Ahli Wad Medani, is a football club in the city of Wad Medani, Sudan. They played in the top level of Sudanese professional football, the Sudan Premier League. Their rival is Ittihad Madani, a team also based in Wad Medani. Al-Ahli (Wad Medani) was founded in 1928.

teams.strTeamAlternate: Al-Ahly Shendi Club, نادي الأهلي شندي
teams.strDescriptionEN:
Al-Ahly Shendi Club (Arabic: نادي الأهلي شندي) is a football (soccer) club from Sudan based in Shendi.

They finished fourth in the 2011 Sudan Premier League. They created big history for the city for the club, for the city of Shendi and for Sudan by progressing to any African competition for the first time and made a record by been drawn with the other Sudanese clubs in the same group and no other country in CAF competitions has represented three

teams.strTeamAlternate: الفلاح عطبرة, Al-Falah Cultural, Social and Sports Club
teams.strDescriptionEN:
Al-Falah Cultural, Social and Sports Club (Arabic: الفلاح عطبرة) is a football club from Atbara, Sudan.

In the 2019–20 season, the club participated in the 2019–20 Sudan Premier League.

teams.strTeamAlternate: Al Hilal Sports Club, نادي الهلال للتربية‎
teams.strDescriptionEN: Al Hilal Sports Club (Arabic: نادي الهلال للتربية), known as Al Hilal S.C or simply Al Hilal, is a Sudanese professional football club based in Omdurman that competes in the Sudan Premier League. The club currently competes in the Super D1, the top-flight of football in Mauritania, due to the War in Sudan.

teams.strTeamAlternate: نادي المريخ الرياضي‎, Al-Merrikh Sporting Club
teams.strDescriptionEN: Al-Merrikh Sporting Club (Arabic: نادي المريخ الرياضي‎) is a Sudanese football club based in Omdurman. Their home stadium is Al-Merrikh Stadium, which is locally known as The Red Castle. Founded in 1908, Al-Merrikh is one of the oldest football clubs in Africa, and have won the Sudan Premier League 16 times and Sudan Cup 14 times. Al-Merrikh is Arabic for Mars. The club share a fierce rivalry with Al-Hilal, the games between them regularly selling out, as well as being the only other realistic challenger to the league crown. Al-Hilal are also based in Omdurman with only Al-Ardha street separating the teams and between them they are Sudan's most powerful and successful football clubs.

teams.strTeamAlternate: Al-Rabita Sports Club, نادي الرابطة الرياضي
teams.strDescriptionEN: Al-Rabita Sports Club (Arabic: نادي الرابطة الرياضي) also known as Al-Rabita Kosti is a Sudanese football club based in Kosti. They play in the second division in Sudanese football, Sudan Second Division.

Alamal Sports Club Atbara (Arabic: نادي الأمل الرياضي عطبره‎) is a Sudanese football club based in Atbara. They play in the top division in Sudanese football, Sudan Premier League. Their home stadium is Stade Al-Amal Atbara.

teams.strTeamAlternate: Haidoub En Nahud, Haidoub SC, نادي حيدوب - النهود

teams.strDescriptionEN: Hay Al-Arab Sports Club (Arabic: نادي حي العرب الرياضي) is a Sudanese football club based in Port Sudan. They play in the top division in Sudanese football, the Sudan Premier League. Their home stadium is Stade Port Sudan. Their rivals is Hilal Al Sahil a team which is in Port Sudan in the same league as Hay Al Arab.

Hilal Alsahil Sports Club (Arabic: نادي هلال الساحل الرياضي) is a Sudanese football club founded in 1937 in Port Sudan. They played in the top division in Sudanese football, Sudan Premier League. Their home stadium is Stade Port Sudan. Their rival is Hay Al Arab, a team also in Port Sudan

Al-Hilal Educational Sport Club (Arabic: نادي الهلال للتربية البدنية) also known as Hilal Al-Fasher is a football club from Al-Fasher, Sudan. They play in the top level of Sudanese professional football, the Sudan Premier League.
